channel.title: Can't connect to a server (PLEASE HELP, PLEASE!)
channel.description:
Ok well I downloaded this server and client on this thread:
http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,391563.0.html
When I run the client, it tells me to type in my ip address. I typed in my static ip, 0.0.0.0, 127.0.0.1, my ip I got off whatismyip.com, and none of them worked. I still get the error_gamejs5connect error. PLEASE HELP any help is appreciated thank you very much.
Edit: blank, 0, and localhost do not work eitheir
Edit2: This is all when I run the client, when I try to run the server I get some other error message with a lot more text. I'll try to copy it down and paste it in a sec.
The error message is:
The system can not find the patch specified. Exception in thread "main" java...

@Crazyjackson78 wrote:

David The Drummer:

Have you compiled [b]every[b] time you change something in your files?

I don’t know what it means. The original poster said I don’t need to change anything for it to run, just enter in an ip for it to connect to when it asks. My problem is no matter what I type in I always get the error_game_js5connect error

item.dc:creator: @M_And_W M And W
item.description:
@M_And_W wrote:

[quote=“Crazyjackson78, post:13, topic:374465”][quote author=David The Drummer link=topic=470439.msg3440375#msg3440375 date=1293052902]

Make sure you’ve set up your environmental variables

This could be my problem, could you please tell me if this is right?

Path: CLASSPATH=C:\Windows\System32;C:\Program Files\Java\Jre6\bin

Classpath:

CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_23\bin;%CLASSPATH%;

Those seem about right, but I’m not for sure because I set mine a long time ago, and haven’t messed with it since. Go brush up on an environmental settings guide and see if you did something wrong.
[/quote]

I changed them, and it still doesn’t work.[/quote]

Setting up the classpath and path would set your java straight, but I’m not seeing how it would affect your IP configuration…
